# read {presets/scripts/index.mk.hint} as ScriptDefaults

Use the shared package and monorepo paths defined by {ScriptDefaults}.

# module testMakefile

Reusable GNU Make include fragment for package-scoped tests, coverage, linting,
and formatting in a JavaScript or TypeScript monorepo. It must not define the
default goal.

# entity TestVariables

Every command and argument list is overrideable with `?=`:

- `VITEST_COMMAND ?= $(PACKAGE_MANAGER) vitest`
- `VITEST_CONFIG ?= $(MONOREPO_ROOT)/vitest.config.ts`
- `TEST_FILTER ?= $(PACKAGE_DIR)`
- `TEST_ARGS ?= run`
- `COVERAGE_ARGS ?= run --coverage`
- `ESLINT_COMMAND ?= $(PACKAGE_MANAGER) eslint`
- `ESLINT_TARGET ?= .`
- `PRETTIER_COMMAND ?= $(PACKAGE_MANAGER) prettier`
- `PRETTIER_TARGET ?= .`

`TEST_FILTER` is a Vitest positional path filter. Its package-directory default
prevents every Turbo package task from rerunning the complete monorepo suite.
Callers may set it to a narrower file, glob, or test name supported by Vitest.

# action test-js

Declare `test-js` phony. From `$(PACKAGE_DIR)`, run:

`$(VITEST_COMMAND) $(TEST_ARGS) --config "$(VITEST_CONFIG)" "$(TEST_FILTER)"`

Do not enable watch mode by default.

# action coverage-js

Declare `coverage-js` phony. From `$(PACKAGE_DIR)`, run:

`$(VITEST_COMMAND) $(COVERAGE_ARGS) --config "$(VITEST_CONFIG)" "$(TEST_FILTER)"`

# action lint-js

Declare `lint-js` phony. From `$(PACKAGE_DIR)`, run:

`$(ESLINT_COMMAND) "$(ESLINT_TARGET)"`

# action fix-js

Declare `fix-js` phony. From `$(PACKAGE_DIR)`, run:

`$(ESLINT_COMMAND) "$(ESLINT_TARGET)" --fix`

# action format-js

Declare `format-js` phony. From `$(PACKAGE_DIR)`, run:

`$(PRETTIER_COMMAND) --write "$(PRETTIER_TARGET)"`

# action refresh-js

Declare `refresh-js` phony and make it depend on `format-js`. Its recipe then
invokes `$(MAKE) fix-js`. This guarantees formatting completes before ESLint
fixes even when the parent Make process uses parallel execution. It is the
package-level normalization target used by existing npm scripts.

# rule

- Each recipe fails when its underlying tool fails.
- Commands execute against one package by default, not the entire monorepo.
- Tool binaries resolve through the workspace package manager.
- CI can append tool-specific options by overriding the corresponding `*_ARGS`
  variable without editing this shared fragment.
